overview: The user wanted to improve the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant began by
  thoroughly reviewing the existing CSS and component styling. Based on this
  analysis, a new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced, replacing
  the previous corporate blue/gray scheme. Key components like the main
  questionnaire form, progress bar, intro section, and report section were
  redesigned with subtle background elements, improved typography, and more
  engaging visual feedback. Form fields like checkboxes, radio buttons, and
  sliders also received significant styling updates to align with the new
  aesthetic. The goal was to transform the app from a "template-driven" look to
  a more professional, trustworthy, and visually appealing interface tailored
  for a sleep health application. After implementing the changes, the assistant
  confirmed successful compilation and proceeded to visually inspect the updated
  app in the browser.
